# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LibraryManagementSystem — Environment Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your own values. .env is gitignored
# and must NEVER be committed.
#
# Each tester registers their own SoundCloud app and uses their own
# credentials. There is no shared/baked-in app — see README.md for the
# 5-minute setup walkthrough.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── SoundCloud OAuth (required for SoundCloud sync features) ─────────────────
#
# 1. Sign in at https://soundcloud.com
# 2. Open https://soundcloud.com/you/apps and click "Register a new app"
# 3. Give it a neutral name (e.g. "Crate Sync — <your name>")
# 4. Set the redirect URI to:    http://127.0.0.1:5001/callback
# 5. Copy the generated Client ID + Client Secret here.

SOUNDCLOUD_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
SOUNDCLOUD_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# Optional — only override if you registered a different redirect URI on
# your SoundCloud app. The local OAuth listener auto-binds to the port
# in this URL.
# SOUNDCLOUD_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:5001/callback
